'''Brynley Francis Roberts''' {{postnominals|country=GBR|CBE|FLSW}} (born 1931), known as '''Bryn Roberts''', is a Welsh scholar and literary critic. He has written extensively on the [[Welsh language]] and [[Celts|Celtic]] history. He was Professor of Welsh Language and Literature at the [[University of Wales, Swansea]] from 1978 to 1975, and Librarian of the [[National Library of Wales]] from 1985 to 1994. He was made editor of the ''[[Dictionary of Welsh Biography]]'' in 1987, and of ''[[Y Traethodydd]]'' in 1999.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abgs.org.uk/FormerPupils/bfroberts/bfr.html |title=Brynley Francis Roberts, CBE, DLitt, MA, PhD, FLSW Scholar of Celtic Studies |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website=Aberdare Boys' Grammar School Former Pupils |publisher= |access-date=11 February 2015}}</ref>
Roberts is a member of the council of the [[Honourable Society of Cymmrodorion]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.cymmrodorion1751.org.uk/pages/officers.html| title=Cyngor a Swyddogion/Council and Officers. Rhagfyr/December 2003| access-date=2009-01-13| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828072141/http://www.cymmrodorion1751.org.uk/pages/officers.html#| archive-date=2008-08-28| dead-url=yes| df=}}</ref> He is also involved in the Morfa Chapel, [[Aberystwyth]], part of the [[Presbyterian Church of Wales]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.capelymorfa.org/swyddogion.html| title=Swyddogion y Capel| language=Welsh}}</ref>
